    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nMost of the `:lsp` subcommands are thin wrappers around functions from `vim.lsp`:\n- `:lsp enable`: `vim.lsp.enable(..., true)`\n- `:lsp disable`: `vim.lsp.enable(..., false)`\n- `:lsp stop`: `Client:stop()`\n\n`:lsp restart` has no non-interactive equivalent, so plugins/configs which wish to programmatically restart a client either have to do it manually or use `vim.cmd.lsp { 'restart', ... }`\n\n### Solution\n\nIntroduce `Client:restart()`. I would be willing to write this myself, but I want to make sure this is a wanted change, as it seems slightly niche.",
